                <note rend="inline" type="source">417.00/325: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-05-25T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 25, 1929—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>80. Your 143, May 21, 4 p.m. If President Moncada wishes to submit a formal
                    request for the designation by this Government of a member of the Claims
                    Commission, stating the terms of employment and giving full information about
                    the manner in which the Commission will be constituted and the powers which it
                    will enjoy, the Department will be very glad to consider the immediate
                    designation of some qualified person. A copy of the decree which the President
                    proposes to issue would be most useful in this connection.</p>
                <p>The Department has not yet been informed how President Moncada proposes to have
                    the Nicaraguan members of the Commission appointed. Please obtain information on
                    this point.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
